The paper discusses inductive logic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus of the paper is on improving the efficiency of ILP systems, which involves optimizing the execution of queries and structuring sets of similar queries. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which often involve querying large datasets. Finally, the paper discusses incorporating query pack execution into existing learning systems, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
